    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/261a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-14T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6889. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 197. Referring our 195, March 12, in addition to other matters mentioned to
                    Dutch Minister, <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1"
                        >McCormick</persName> also conveyed to him that even in case United States
                    and Allies were obliged to requisition, Holland’s trade with her colonies would
                    be facilitated. This is very important to allay the fears of Holland as to her
                    colonial trade.</p>
                <p>Repeat to <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SRB1">Stevens</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1">Garrett</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
